==Old English==
===Etymology===
From a variant base of [[wrecan]].

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/wræk/}}

===Noun===
'''wræc''' ''n'' (plural '''[[wræcu]]''')
# [[misery]], [[torment]]
#:''Ende næfre ðines wræces weorþeþ.''  Your sufferings will never end.
# [[persecution]], [[punishment]]
# [[exile]]
#:''Wilfriþ æfter langum wræce wæs eft onfangen on bisceop-had.''  After a long exile, Wilfrith was received back into bishophood.  (Bede)

===Descendants===
*English [[wrack]]

